      Description

      Go, Dog. Go! is a 1961 children's book written and illustrated by P. D. Eastman. It describes the actions and interactions of a group of highly mobile dogs, who operate cars and other conveyances in pursuit of work, play, and a final mysterious goal: a dog party. Wikipedia
      Originally published: March 12, 1961
      Author: P. D. Eastman
      Illustrator: Philip D. Eastman
      Preceded by: Are You My Mother?
      Followed by: Hand, Hand, Fingers, Thumb
      Genres: Fiction, Children's literature
